divs: Sighting DetailsI thought that the activity was over but after reporting my sightings of the five, or two, crafts, I thought the activity was over. I went in to report those. Afterward I can back outside and at 12:24am I looked straight up and there was another star moving. It fired two bursts of, whatever they do, and it moved northward across the night sky until it disappeared or faded out . . . or . . . whatever it is they do. Just seems like the activity is picking up like last year about this time when I had over 33 sightings between June 27th and November 3rd. Keep looking up in the sky Redding.
Summary: A star craft; two bursts and it was gone
